<TITLE> Police nab Bangla Bhai's associates </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Naogaon, May 03 (bdnews24.com) Naogaon police on Monday arrested two chief aides of Siddiqul Islam, alias Bangla Bhai, a leader of the banned militant Islamist outfit Jamaat-ul-Mujahideen Bangladesh (JMB). The arrested militants are ATM Ali Jinnah, 55, and his son Jamal Uddin, 25 of Shafikpur village under Raninagar upazila. Naogaon police superintendent Mofazzel Hossain told bdnews24.com that the two were absconding in a number of cases that include abduction and murder. Jinnah and Jamal were sent to police custody after primary interrogation, the official said. Bangla Bhai and his associates, on May 18, 2004, kidnapped a Juba League leader Idris Ali Khejur and took him to Bheti camp, Hossain said. They were also accused for being involved in the killing of alleged extremist leader Abdul Qaium Badshah, the police officer said. bdne
